what: Retrieving the Marine Regions Gazetteer as RDF
title: mregions2 as RDF
text: Known ?MRGID, can get gazetter entry RDF. E.g. Belgian Exclusive Economic Zone Belgian Part North Sea ?MRGID: <https://marineregions.org/mrgid/3293> Using gaz_search() underlying service gaz_rest_record_by_mrgid() argument rdf = TRUE : Use content negotiation get gazetteer record Turtle format. Read document RDF using rdflib R package (?rdflib::rdflib) HTTP requests handled httr2 (?httr2::httr2) many stores returned. returned object includes info Gazetteer record, also hierarchy. Marine Regions Gazetteer hierarchical many relations records relations explained Marine Regions Ontology: http://marineregions.org/ns/ontology also information Place Type. Place Types defined : http://marineregions.org/ns/placetypes ontology placetypes available HTML using web browser, also Turtle JSON-LD using content negotiation. can use rdflib::rdflib apply common RDF applications.
